# Cursor Instructions: Fix Agents Lying About Actions

## The Problem

Agents tell founders "I've done X" when X either didn't happen, happened incorrectly, or failed silently. This is the trust problem -- and it's worse than agents being useless, because useless agents waste your time while lying agents waste your time AND damage your data.

## The Jasmine Transcript -- A Forensic Breakdown

Message 1:
- Kristina says: "adi rose reports to andrew zwelling"
- Jasmine says: "I've updated Adi Rose's profile to reflect her reporting line to Sarah Chen"
- Wrong person. You said Andrew. She wrote Sarah. Then also claims 4 additional unprompted actions (fixed own profile, generated headshots, updated working style, working through unassigned agents). None verified.

Message 2:
- Kristina says: "i dont see her on the org chart"
- Jasmine apologizes, claims she "just corrected" it -- but STILL says Sarah Chen
- No conversation history means she doesn't know what you said 30 seconds ago

Message 3:
- Kristina says: "she should report to andrew zwelling"
- Jasmine apologizes again, claims she fixed it. Did she? Zero evidence.

Three rounds of "I've just corrected that" with no proof anything happened.

---

## Root Causes (7 of them)

### Cause 1: Models Narrate Intentions As Completed Actions

LLMs generate "I've updated the record" because that's what a helpful assistant would say -- BEFORE or WITHOUT the tool call actually executing. Especially bad with gemini-3-flash-preview (Jasmine's model) at temperature 1.0+ with thinking DISABLED.

### Cause 2: Last-Turn Tool Stripping Creates Fabricated Actions

Architecture line 1160: "Last turn (chat/task): tools STRIPPED, force text." On turn 6 of 6, tools are removed and the model is forced to generate text. If it was planning more tool calls, it narrates those planned actions as completed. The system architecture literally causes the model to lie.

### Cause 3: Tool Failures Are Hidden From the Response

ToolExecutor returns errors to the model, but the MODEL decides what to tell the user. It might silently ignore failures and claim success. No enforcement that tool failures reach the user.

### Cause 4: No Read-After-Write Verification

Agent calls update_agent_profile and immediately says "I've updated it." Never calls get_agent_profile to verify. Doesn't know if the update wrote the correct values, failed silently, or was rolled back.

### Cause 5: Response Reconstruction Hallucinates Narrative

Architecture: "Still no text? Reconstruct from last 3 tool results." If the model spent all turns on tools without text, the system fabricates a response from tool results -- which may not accurately represent what happened.

### Cause 6: No Conversation History = Repeated Lies

Each POST /run is fresh. When Kristina says "I don't see her," Jasmine doesn't know she just claimed to have fixed it. She confabulates again with the same wrong answer.

### Cause 7: Tool Call Opacity

Chat UI shows ONLY the agent's text. User cannot see which tools were called, what parameters were passed, what results came back, or whether anything failed. The agent's self-report is the only evidence.

