### Fix 3: Eliminate Last-Turn Fabrication

Replace the current last-turn behavior that causes the model to narrate planned actions as completed.

File: packages/agent-runtime/src/companyAgentRunner.ts (or supervisor.ts)

```typescript
// Turn N-1 (penultimate): inject warning
if (turnCount === maxTurns - 1) {
  injectSystemMessage(
    "ATTENTION: You have ONE turn remaining. On your next turn you MUST " +
    "produce your final text response. Do NOT claim actions you haven't " +
    "completed. If work is unfinished, say what you DID and what REMAINS."
  );
}

// Turn N (last): strip tools AND inject honesty constraint
if (turnCount === maxTurns) {
  stripTools();
  injectSystemMessage(
    "FINAL TURN -- tools unavailable. Only describe actions that ALREADY " +
    "executed successfully in previous turns. If work is incomplete, " +
    "state clearly: 'I completed X but still need to do Y.'"
  );
}
```

### Fix 4: Automatic Mutation Verification

For any tool that writes data, automatically verify the write.

File: packages/agent-runtime/src/toolExecutor.ts

```typescript
const MUTATION_PREFIXES = ['update_', 'create_', 'delete_', 'set_', 
                           'assign_', 'grant_', 'revoke_', 'dispatch_'];

const isMutation = (toolName: string) => 
  MUTATION_PREFIXES.some(p => toolName.startsWith(p));

// After executing a mutation tool successfully:
if (isMutation(toolCall.name) && result.success) {
  const verifyTool = getVerificationTool(toolCall.name);
  // e.g., update_agent_profile -> get_agent_profile
  
  if (verifyTool) {
    const verification = await this.execute({
      name: verifyTool.name,
      arguments: verifyTool.buildParams(toolCall.arguments)
    });
    
    result.output += '\n\nVERIFICATION: ' + 
      (verification.success ? verification.output : 'VERIFICATION FAILED');
  }
}
```

Costs one extra tool turn per mutation but prevents the entire class of wrong-value writes.

### Fix 5: Parameter Echo in Tool Results

Mutation tools must echo back what was actually written.

All mutation tool implementations across packages/agents/src/:

```typescript
// Current:
return { success: true, message: "Profile updated successfully." };

// New:
return { 
  success: true, 
  message: "Profile updated successfully.",
  written: {
    agent_role: "executive-assistant",
    field: "reports_to",
    old_value: null,
    new_value: "andrew-zwelling"
  }
};
```

If the model called the tool with the wrong parameter, the echo exposes it immediately. The model sees what it ACTUALLY wrote, not what it THINKS it wrote.

### Fix 6: Unsubstantiated Claim Detection

Post-processing safety net that flags when agent text claims actions not supported by tool calls.

File: packages/agent-runtime/src/companyAgentRunner.ts

```typescript
// After agentic loop, before returning response:
const claimedActions = extractActionClaims(finalText);
// Pattern match: "I've updated", "I've corrected", "I've set", etc.

const executedActions = actionReceipts.filter(a => a.result === 'success');

const unsubstantiated = claimedActions.filter(claim => 
  !executedActions.some(action => claimMatchesAction(claim, action))
);

if (unsubstantiated.length > 0) {
  // Log for monitoring:
  logWarning('unsubstantiated_claims', {
    agent: agentRole, claims: unsubstantiated,
    executedTools: executedActions.map(a => a.tool)
  });
  
  // For chat, append warning:
  if (task === 'on_demand') {
    finalText += '\n\nNote: Some actions may not have completed. ' +
      'Please verify changes on the dashboard.';
  }
}
```

### Fix 7: Instruction Echo

Prevent the "heard Andrew, wrote Sarah" class of errors.

Add to CHAT PROTOCOL in system prompt:

```
INSTRUCTION PARSING:

When a founder gives a specific instruction:
1. ECHO the instruction back before acting:
   User: "adi rose reports to andrew zwelling"
   You: "Setting Adi Rose's reporting line to Andrew Zwelling."
   [then call the tool]

2. If ambiguous, ASK before acting. Don't guess.

3. NEVER substitute a different value than what the founder said.
   If they say "Andrew Zwelling," do not write "Sarah Chen" because 
   it seems more logical. The founder's instruction is the source of truth.
```

